{"title_page": "Rocky Dawuni", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Rocky Dawuni\n| image               = Rocky Dawuni.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| landscape           = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = \n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1969|01|22}}\n| birth_place         = Ghana\n| origin              = \n| death_date          = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) -->\n| death_place         = \n| genre               = \n| occupation          = Musician and Activist\n| instrument          = \n| years_active        = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = \n| website             =  {{url|www.rockydawuni.com}} \n}}\n'''Rocky Dawuni''' (born January 22, 1969) is a [[Ghana]]ian singer, songwriter and record producer who performs his signature ''''Afro Roots'''' sound which is a mixture of Reggae, Afrobeat, Highlife and soul music. He currently lives between Ghana and Los Angeles.<ref name=\"cnn\">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/SHOWBIZ/Music/08/23/rocky.dawuni.ghana.reggae/|title='Ghana's Bob Marley' spreads message of brotherhood|date=23 August 2011|publisher=CNN|accessdate=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nDawuni got acquainted with Reggae in Ghana when he heard a military band performing one of [[Bob Marley]]'s compositions in Michel Camp;<ref>{{cite web|title=Rocky grew up in Michel Camp, Ghana|url=http://www.katc.com/clip/12388196/festival-international-friday-at-1000|publisher=katc.com|accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref> a [[military barracks]] where he grew up in Ghana.<ref name=\"cnn\"/> Dawuni started the annual \"Independence Splash\" festival, which was held in Ghana on [[Independence Day (Ghana)|Ghanaian Independence Day]], March 6.<ref name=\"cnn\"/>\n\nDawuni had recorded seven full-length albums by 2019.<ref name=\"cnn\"/> His sixth studio album titled '''Branches of The Same Tree''' for a [[Grammy Award for Best Reggae Album]] in December 2015 for the [[58th Annual Grammy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Branches of the Same Tree album|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/branches-of-the-same-tree/id963525098|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=10 December 2015}}</ref> released 31 March 2015 was nominated the first nominee from his home country of Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-in-historic%E2%80%8B-nomination-for-58th%E2%80%8B-grammy/|title=Rocky nominated for a Grammy|publisher=theafricandream.net|accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref> '''Beats of Zion''', the 2019 single of Rocky which was released January 25 <ref>{{cite web|title=2019 single release|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-2019-single-beats-of-zion/|publisher=TheAfricanDream.net|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref> is a precursor to his 7th studio album which also bears the same title.<ref>{{cite web|title=2019 album|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-beats-of-zion-album-ft-stonebwoy-sarkodie-alika-wiyaala/|publisher=TheAfricanDream.net|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Beats of Zion|url=https://www.popmatters.com/rocky-dawuni-beats-of-zion-2626635597.html|publisher=PopMatters|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Beats of Zion album|url=https://medium.com/@doctorradic/premiere-rocky-dawuni-unveils-wickedest-sound-ft-stonebwoy-d4595c1af29e|publisher=PopMatters|accessdate=22 June 2019}}</ref>\nIn June 2019 Rocky released the new single \"Modern Man\", remixed by [[Gaudi (musician)|Gaudi]].\n\n==Activism and goodwill==\n\nThe musician and activist who is known to straddle the boundaries between Africa, the Caribbean and the U.S. to create sounds that unite generations and cultures works to foster global peace. Dawuni has shared the stage with\u00a0[[Stevie Wonder]],\u00a0[[Peter Gabriel]],\u00a0[[Bono]],\u00a0[[Jason Mraz]],\u00a0[[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]]\u00a0and\u00a0[[John Legend]], among many others. Named one of Africa's Top 10 global stars by [[CNN]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rocky featured on CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2011/SHOWBIZ/Music/08/23/rocky.dawuni.ghana.reggae/index.html|publisher=cnn.com|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nDawuni's stature as a cultural diplomat and successful melding of music and activism have led him to become a spokesperson for various global causes. He is a [[United Nations]] [[Goodwill Ambassador]] for Africa for UN Environment<ref>{{cite web|title=UN Goodwill Ambassador|url=https://www.unenvironment.org/people/rocky-dawuni|publisher=unenvironment.org|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref> and is a Global Ambassador for the UN Foundation's Clean Cooking Alliance alongside actress [[Julia Roberts]] and Chef [[Jos\u00e9 Andr\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rocky works with Clean Cook Alliance|url=https://cleancookingalliance.org/about/champions/62.html|publisher=cleancookingalliance.org|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rocky Clean Cook Alliance|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-joins-hillary-clinton-and/?preview=true|publisher=theafricandream.net|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Album !! Year\n|-\n| The Movement || 1996\n|-\n| Crusade || 1998\n|-\n| Awakening || 2001\n|-\n| Book of Changes || 2005 <ref>{{cite web|title=Book of Changes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/book-of-changes/id110745860|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Hymns for the Rebel Soul || 2010\n|-\n| Branches of The Same Tree || 2015 <ref>{{cite web|title=Branches of The Same Tree at 58th Grammys|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees?genre=29|publisher=Grammy|accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Beats of Zion || 2019 <ref>{{cite web|title=7th album|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-beats-of-zion-album-ft-stonebwoy-sarkodie-alika-wiyaala/|publisher=TheAfricanDream.net|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Videography==\n{{Expand list|date=February 2016}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Director\n!Ref\n|-\n|2010\n|''Walk The Talk''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Walk The Talk video|url=https://sonichits.com/video/Rocky_Dawuni/Walk_The_Talk|website=sonichits.com|accessdate=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2010\n|''African Reggae Fever''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=African Reggae Fever video|url=https://rastafari.tv/video/rocky-dawuni-african-reggae-fever/|website=rastafari.tv|accessdate=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2010\n|''Download The Reveolution''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Sownload The Revolution video|url=https://biafranunity.tv/music/download-the-revolution/|website=biafranunity.tv|accessdate=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015\n|''Nairobi''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Music Video Rocky Dawuni - Nairobi|url=http://pulse.com.gh/music-videos/music-video-rocky-dawuni-nairobi-id4095411.html|website=Pulse.com.gh|publisher=David Mawuli|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015\n|''African Thriller''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=African Thriller video|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/new-rocky-dawuni-album-out-march-31-2015/|website=TheAfricanDream.net|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|''Shine a Light''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Shine a Light video|url=https://www.axs.com/rocky-dawuni-premieres-joyful-video-for-shine-a-light-113520|website=www.axs.com|accessdate=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''Beats of Zion''\n|{{N/A}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Beats of Zion video|url=https://www.theafricandream.net/rocky-dawuni-2019-single-beats-of-zion/|website=TheAfricanDream.net|accessdate=26 January 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Music featured in movies ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Soundtrack !! Movie title !! Movie Genre\n|-\n| Shine a Light || [[Fist Fight]] || [[Comedy]]\n|}\n\n== Music featured on television ==\n\n{| class=\"