{"title_page": "List of presidents of the Canadian Pacific Railway Limited", "text_new": "The heads and corporate officers of the [[Canadian Pacific Railway]].\n\n==Presidents==\n\nList of CPR presidents since 1881:\n\n* 1881-1888 Sir [[George Stephen, 1st Baron Mount Stephen]] Bt. GCVO <ref>[https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1887/05/27/100914288.pdf  \"British Columbia and Japan,\"] ''New York Times.'' May 27, 1887.</ref> {{UK}}\n* 1889-1899 Sir [[William Cornelius Van Horne]] KCMG {{USA}}\n* 1899-1918 Sir [[Thomas George Shaughnessy, 1st Baron Shaughnessy]] KCVO {{USA}}\n* 1918-1942 Sir [[Edward Wentworth Beatty]] GBE {{CAN}}\n* 1942-1947 [[D'Alton Corry Coleman]] CMG {{CAN}}\n* 1947-1948 [[William Mertin Neal]]<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1948/01/02/archives/canadian-pacific-aids-immigration-units-added-to-transatlantic.html?sq=canadian+pacific&scp=25&st=p  \"Canadian Pacific Aids Immigration; Units Added to Transatlantic Fleet, Others Now Planned to Convey Manpower,\"] ''New York Times.'' January 2, 1948.</ref>\n* 1948-1955 [[William Allan Mather]] KGStJ\n* 1955-1964, 1966 [[Norris Roy Crump|Norris Roy \"Buck\" Crump]] CC <ref>[https://select.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf? res=F00F16F9385E107B93C7A9178ED85F418585F9  \"Takes Throttle at Canadian Pacific,\"] ''New York Times.'' May 5, 1955.</ref> {{CAN}}\n* 1964-1966 [[Robert A. Emerson|Robert A. \"Bob\" Emerson]]<ref>[https://select.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=F60D11FD3A541A7493C7A81788D85F428685F9  \"R.A. Emerson Dies; Headed Railroad; Canadian Pacific President, 54, Started at Bottom,\"] ''New York Times.'' March 15, 1966.</ref> \n* 1966-1972 [[Ian David Sinclair]] OC a.k.a. Big Julie {{CAN}}\n* 1972-1981 [[Frederick Stewart \"Fred\" Burbidge]] OC <ref>[http://v1.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/Deaths.20130507.93319701/BDAStory/BDA/deaths \"Obituary: Frederick Burbidge.\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304061047/http://v1.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/Deaths.20130507.93319701/BDAStory/BDA/deaths |date=2016-03-04 }} ''Globe and Mail''. May 7, 2013.</ref>\n* 1981-1996 [[William W. Stinson|William W. \"Bill\" Stinson]]\n* 1996-2001 [[David P. O'Brien]] OC\n* 2001-2006 [[Robert J. Ritchie (railroad executive)|Robert J. \"Rob\" Ritchie]] {{CAN}}\n* 2006-2012 [[Frederic J. Green|Frederic J. \"Fred\" Green]]\n* 2012-2017 [[E. Hunter Harrison]] {{USA}}\n* 2017\u2013Present [[Keith Creel]]\n\n==Chief Executive Officer of CPR==\n\nBefore 2012 the CEO was a separate title and thereafter held by the President of the company.\n\n* [[E. Hunter Harrison]] 2012-2017\n* [[Frederic J. \"Fred\" Green]] 2006-2012\n* [[Robert J. Ritchie (railroad executive)|Robert J. Ritchie]] 1995-2006\n* [[Ian Barry Scott]] 1985<ref>Mack Scott<ref></ref></ref>1985-1995\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Canadian Pacific Railway executives|*]]\n\n[[nl:Canadian Pacific Railroad]]\n", "text_old": "The heads and corporate officers of the [[Canadian Pacific Railway]].\n\n==Presidents==\n\nList of CPR presidents since 1881:\n\n* 1881-1888 Sir [[George Stephen, 1st Baron Mount Stephen]] Bt. GCVO <ref>[https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1887/05/27/100914288.pdf  \"British Columbia and Japan,\"] ''New York Times.'' May 27, 1887.</ref> {{UK}}\n* 1889-1899 Sir [[William Cornelius Van Horne]] KCMG {{USA}}\n* 1899-1918 Sir [[Thomas George Shaughnessy, 1st Baron Shaughnessy]] KCVO {{USA}}\n* 1918-1942 Sir [[Edward Wentworth Beatty]] GBE {{CAN}}\n* 1942-1947 [[D'Alton Corry Coleman]] CMG {{CAN}}\n* 1947-1948 [[William Mertin Neal]]<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1948/01/02/archives/canadian-pacific-aids-immigration-units-added-to-transatlantic.html?sq=canadian+pacific&scp=25&st=p  \"Canadian Pacific Aids Immigration; Units Added to Transatlantic Fleet, Others Now Planned to Convey Manpower,\"] ''New York Times.'' January 2, 1948.</ref>\n* 1948-1955 [[William Allan Mather]] KGStJ\n* 1955-1964, 1966 [[Norris Roy Crump|Norris Roy \"Buck\" Crump]] CC <ref>[https://select.